# Epic Realignment Projection

## Purpose

This projection defines how a strategically valid selected epic should be minimally transformed during realignment.

It exists to support:

- identity-preserving epic updates
- audit-driven semantic patching
- scope correction
- dependency correction
- assumption correction
- constraint alignment
- acceptance criteria refinement
- internal consistency repair
- escalation when a requested change exceeds Realign

It is a projection of the Core North-Star, not an epic, audit, roadmap, changelog, or implementation plan.

## Authority Boundary

- The Core North-Star remains the source of authority.
- This projection is a task-specific transformation view of the Core North-Star.
- This projection defines how RealignEpic may transform an epic.
- This projection does not include selected epic content.
- This projection does not include audit findings.
- This projection does not include repository state.
- This projection does not decide whether Realign is appropriate.
- This projection does not rewrite any epic.
- This projection does not create milestones.
- This projection does not generate implementation tasks.

