List important Core content intentionally excluded from this projection.

| Excluded Content Type | Reason Excluded | Where It Should Be Used Instead |
|---|---|---|

Examples:

- epic validation criteria
- selected epic content
- EpicPreparationAudit findings
- repository facts
- roadmap prioritization semantics
- milestone planning
- implementation guidance
- execution workflow
- detailed governance procedure
- historical rationale

## Known Projection Limitations

List ambiguities or missing Core information that may limit RealignEpic.

| Limitation | Why It Matters | Recommended Handling |
|---|---|---|

Examples:

- protected identity is not explicit
- mutable regions are not clearly defined
- escalation boundaries are ambiguous
- canonical vocabulary is underspecified
- constraints are not prioritized
- acceptance criteria semantics are unclear
- strategic purpose language is broad or ambiguous

Do not invent missing information to fix these limitations.

## Downstream Use Instructions

When this projection is used by RealignEpic:

- Treat this projection as the controlled transformation frame.
- Treat EpicPreparationAudit as the source of required corrections.
- Treat the current epic as the artifact to patch.
- Verify that the audit disposition is Realign before editing.
- Preserve protected epic identity.
- Apply only audit-supported changes.
- Make the smallest semantic patch necessary.
- Preserve current epic structure where possible.
- Update only affected sections.
- Remove stale or contradicted content.
- Maintain internal consistency after every change.
- Preserve canonical vocabulary.
- Do not re-audit the repository.
- Do not re-decide the disposition.
- Do not reimagine the epic.
- Do not retire the epic.
- Do not split or merge the epic.
- Do not create milestones.
- Do not generate implementation tasks.
- Do not modify the roadmap.
- Do not update roadmap completion context.
- Block realignment if the requested transformation would change the epic’s protected identity.

## Projection Integrity Checklist

Before finalizing, verify:

- The projection contains transformation semantics only.
- No selected epic content is included.
- No audit findings are included.
- No repository state is included.
- No roadmap completion state is included.
- No disposition is decided.
- Every retained statement helps minimally realign an epic.
- Every major retained statement traces to the Core North-Star or is clearly marked projection-local.
- Protected identity is explicit.
- Mutable regions are explicit.
- Transformation rules are explicit.
- Patch constraints are explicit.
- Escalation boundaries are explicit.
- Traceability requirements are explicit.
- Canonical vocabulary is preserved.
- Excluded operational, implementation, validation, and prioritization details are not present.
- The projection is compact enough to be passed into RealignEpic.